The paper proposes NLPExplorer, a portal for indexing, searching, and visualizing Natural Language Processing (NLP) research volume. The paper discusses the use of NLP techniques and presents insights from papers, authors, venues, and topics. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also mentions the use of machine learning techniques, which suggests sub-categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the use of search algorithms, which suggests sub-categories such as cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper mentions the use of datasets, which suggests sub-categories such as cs.CY (Computers and Society).
